@page "/about-me"

<PageTitle>B C Williams | Dev - About Me</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="About me page for B C Williams | Dev" />
</HeadContent>


<div class="flex flex-col items-center space-y-12">
    @foreach(var para in paragraphs.OrderBy(para => para.Order))
    {
        <div>
            <h4 class="inline-block text-xl pl-4 md:pl-0 scroll-mt-24" id="@para.Header.Replace(" ", "").ToLower()">
                <span class="font-display text-2xl tracking-wide text-shadow dark:text-slate-50">
                    @para.Header
                </span>
                <hr class="heading-accent mt-2 mb-2 rounded-full border-2 border-accent">
            </h4>
            <div class="bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-900 md:rounded-lg md:shadow-md py-4">
                @for(int i = 0; i < para.BodyText.Length; i++)
                {
                    <p class=@($"{(i == 0 ? "indent-8 " : string.Empty)}max-w-prose px-4 font-[450] md:px-8 py-2 whitespace-pre-wrap")>
                        @para.BodyText[i]
                    </p>
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    }
</div>

@code {
    (UInt16 Order, string Header, string[] BodyText)[] paragraphs = {
        (0, "What I Bring", [
        "I believe that the best qualities I bring to any team or project are: a detail oriented nature, a passionate and driven work ethic, endless curiosity, and the absolute need for continuous self improvement."
        ]),
        (1, "A Little Background",[
        "I've been a programmer at heart since high school. We built frogger in Visual Basic, got the basics of HTML and CSS, and learned the old Macromedia suite by creating WYSIWYG websites with Dreamweaver and filling them with terrible flash animations.",
        "After that I went on to pursue a career in theatre and events attending universities in th US and NZ. After I graduated from Te Kura Toi Whakaari New Zealand Drama School I spent about 12 years in concert and event production. I held roles as a warehouse manager, rigger, outdoor event structure designer, and then finally a technical manager.",
        "I picked up coding again in 2020 as the world of live events ground to a halt. I rediscovered a love of it through Codecademy's online course in Python 3 and have been studying everything I can get my hands on since then.",
        "In 2022 I attended the Coding Dojo Full-Time Software Development Bootcamp and learned full stack basics in C# .NET, MERN, and Python w/Flask. They helped me fall in love with C# after quite a few years of sticking to Python, and since then my love of coding has only grown as I take on both personal and professional projects."
        ]),
        (2, "My Stack",[
        "I am primarily a .NET developer writing software in C#. In general I use Blazor Server or WASM for UI, Entity Framework Core for database interactions, and SQL Server or MySQL for persistence.",
        "My other experience includes: \r\n - .NET MVC with MySQL\r\n - Python with Flask and MySQL\r\n - React.js served by Express.js with MongoDB"
        ]),
        (UInt16.MaxValue, "Hobbies & Intrigues",[
        "In my free time, I enjoy working on personal projects and learning new technologies. I am always looking for new challenges and opportunities to expand my skill set.",
        "My most recent personal projects have been with .NET MAUI and the .NET nanoFramework. I have been experimenting with nanoFramework on an ESP32 to learn a bit about embedded systems and MAUI to learn about app development. My goal is to built some small automations around my home and a MAUI app to interact with them."
        ]),
    };
}
